The paper deals with efficient management and processing of massive amounts of data from diverse sources, which is a common problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The focus on de-duplication and compression also suggests a potential fit for cryptography and security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of theoretical analysis and empirical evaluation aligns with machine learning (cs.LG).
